BT 1 0 0 1 0 75 Tm 12 TL /F1 9 Tf 0 0 0 rg (Language is typically framed as the medium of thought and the carrier of consciousness. This paper argues the opposite:) Tj T* /F2 9 Tf (internal language \(the narrative voice\) is the primary measurement apparatus of the mind, and measurement) Tj T* (causes decoherence.) Tj /F1 9 Tf ( Each word in the internal monologue is a projection operator that collapses the superposition of) Tj T* (undifferentiated experience into a discrete labeled state. The Anti-Zeno effect \(Paper 50\) proves that measurement at rates) Tj T* (exceeding the environmental spectral density accelerates decoherence. The human internal monologue runs at 150-400) Tj T* (words per minute -- 2.5 to 6.7 measurement events per second -- well into the anti-Zeno acceleration regime for neural) Tj T* (coherence.) Tj T* ET
